<sect2 id="sec.prep.powerlinux.powerkvm">
 <title>Preparing for Installation on IBM &powerlinux; Servers with IBM &powerkvm;</title><indexterm>
 <primary>preparation</primary>
 <secondary>PowerLinux</secondary></indexterm>
 <para>
  This section covers the preparatory steps for installing &slsreg; on
  IBM &powerlinux; systems with &powerkvm;. It explains the installation
  from an ISO image with the Kimchi Web interface.<!-- built-in CD-ROM
  drive and over the network.-->  Kimchi is a tool for administrating
  IBM &powerkvm;.
 </para>
 <para>
  This section assumes you have &powerkvm; running on your IBM
  &powerlinux; server.  If &powerkvm; is not pre-installed see
  <quote>Configuring IBM PowerKVM on Power Systems</quote> on <ulink
  url="http://www-01.ibm.com/support/knowledgecenter/linuxonibm/liabp/liabpkickoff.htm"/>
  for installing and setting up &powerkvm;.
 </para>
 <!--
 <sect3 id="sec.prep.eserver.features6x0">
  <title>Modern Features of IBM eServer p5 Systems</title>
  <para>
   IBM eServer p5 systems offer the possibility of partitioning the system.
   This enables the concurrent operation of up to 254 operating systems on
   one machine. These operating systems are installed in
   <emphasis>LPARs</emphasis> (logical partitions). One or several of these
   partitions can contain a &sls; environment.
  </para>
  <para>
   To prepare an LPAR for &sls;, first configure the system over the
   <emphasis>HMC</emphasis>. Refer to the IBM documentation for details:
   <ulink
  url="http://publib.boulder.ibm.com/infocenter/systems/scope/hw/topic/iphbi/iphbikickoff.htm"/>
  </para>
 </sect3>
